<h1 class="text-center">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p> 
This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how DotActual (Pty) Ltd ("Company," "we," or "us") collects, uses, and protects 
the personal information of users ("you" or "users") when using the CramDown mobile application ("App") 
and website ("Website"). We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal
information. By using the App and Website, you consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information 
as described in this Policy.
</p>

<h4>1. Information We Collect:</h4>
<p>a. Personal Information: When you create an account, we collect personal information such as your name, email address, and contact details.</p>
<p>b. Location Information: With your consent, we may collect your device's location information to provide you with location-based services.</p>
<p>c. Transaction Information: We collect information related to your buying and selling activities on the App, including transaction details, payment information, and communications between users.</p>
<p>d. Log Data: We automatically collect certain information when you use the App and Website, such as your IP address, device information, and usage data.</p>
    
<h4>2. Use of Information:</h4>
<p>a. We use your personal information to provide, maintain, and improve the functionality of the App and Website, as well as to personalize your experience.</p>
<p>b. We may use your email address to send you transactional and promotional communications related to CramDown. You can opt-out of promotional emails at any time.</p>
<p>c. We may use aggregated and anonymized data for analytical purposes, to improve our services, and for marketing and advertising purposes.</p>
<p>d. We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties without your explicit consent.</p>

<h4>3. Disclosure of Information:</h4>
<p>a. We may share your personal information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App and 
Website, performing functions on our behalf, or providing services to you.</p>
<p>b. We may disclose your information if required by law, to enforce our Terms and Conditions, or to protect the
rights, property, or safety of the Company, its users, or others.</p>
<p>c. In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your personal information may be
 transferred as part of the transaction, subject to applicable privacy laws.</p>

<h4>4. Data Security:</h4>
<p>a. We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure,
alteration, or destruction.</p>
<p>b. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security due to the inherent
risks associated with electronic transmission and storage.</p>
    
<h4>5. Children's Privacy:</h4>
<p>a. The App and Website are not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal 
information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child, please contact us to 
request deletion.</p>

<h4>6. Third-Party Links and Services:</h4>
<p>a. The App and Website may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not owned or controlled by the Company.
This Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party sites or services. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of such
third parties.
</p>

<h4>7. Changes to the Privacy Policy:</h4>
<p>a. We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any material changes 
through the App, Website, or via email. Your continued use of the App and Website after the changes are implemented 
constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy
</p>

